    <item>
      <title>Getting started</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/install/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/install/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here are a couple of things that we need to do prior to the model experiments.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-toc gdoc-toc__level--3&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#installing-mitgcm&#34;&gt;Installing MITgcm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#testing-mitgcm&#34;&gt;Testing MITgcm&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#configuring-the-system&#34;&gt;configuring the system&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#compile&#34;&gt;compile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#run&#34;&gt;run&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#python&#34;&gt;python&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#miniconda&#34;&gt;miniconda&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#python-package&#34;&gt;python package&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#jupyterlab&#34;&gt;JupyterLab&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;      &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;installing-mitgcm&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Installing MITgcm&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/install/#installing-mitgcm&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Installing MITgcm&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Installing MITgcm&#34; href=&#34;#installing-mitgcm&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://mitgcm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/getting_started/getting_started.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;MITgcm documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- - [Installing MITgcm on OSX by Jody Klymak](https://jklymak.github.io/MITgcmExampleSteadyGauss/install.html)&#xA;- [Installing MITgcm on OSX by Clark Richards](https://www.clarkrichards.org/2022/01/21/first-try-running-mitgcm/) --&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;testing-mitgcm&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Testing MITgcm&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/install/#testing-mitgcm&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Testing MITgcm&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Testing MITgcm&#34; href=&#34;#testing-mitgcm&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;MITgcm includes a set of examples that can be run straight out of the box. For example, you can try to follow the documentation on &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://mitgcm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/examples/barotropic_gyre/barotropic_gyre.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;barotropic gyre&lt;/a&gt; and see you can run the model without an issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>atmosphere</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/atmos/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/atmos/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;MITgcm includes an atmospheric physics as a package and it is in &lt;code&gt;aim_v23&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;The following is the description of this package you can find in &lt;code&gt;MITgcm/pkg/aim_v23&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;gdoc-hint note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__title flex align-center&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;aim_v23_description.tex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__text&#34;&gt;Package &lt;code&gt;aim_v23&lt;/code&gt; contains code for an intermediate complexity atmospheric&#xA;physics scheme derived from the physics in the SPEEDY model of Franco Molteni.&#xA;The package contains the SPEEDY physics routines, re-cast to work with pressure&#xA;coordinate dynamics, together with code that interfaces the SPEEDY&#xA;internal arrays to the MITgcm dynamical kernel.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The following is the description of the verification named &lt;code&gt;aim.5l_cs&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://mitgcm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/examples/examples.html#additional-example-experiments-forward-model-setups&#34;&#xA;&gt;MITgcm&amp;rsquo;s user manual&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>ocean</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/ocean/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/ocean/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a verification called &lt;code&gt;global_ocean.cs32x15&lt;/code&gt; that uses the same grid as &lt;code&gt;aim.5l_cs&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;So, let&amp;rsquo;s get used to it before trying the atmosphere-ocean coupled model.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-toc gdoc-toc__level--3&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#description-of-this-experiment&#34;&gt;description of this experiment&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#compile&#34;&gt;compile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#preparation&#34;&gt;preparation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#model-integration&#34;&gt;model integration&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#analysis&#34;&gt;analysis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#additional-experiments&#34;&gt;additional experiments&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#adding-age-tracer&#34;&gt;adding age tracer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#simulation-with-sea-ice-package&#34;&gt;simulation with sea-ice package&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;      &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;description-of-this-experiment&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        description of this experiment&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/ocean/#description-of-this-experiment&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: description of this experiment&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: description of this experiment&#34; href=&#34;#description-of-this-experiment&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The description of this example is provided in the &lt;code&gt;README&lt;/code&gt; file.&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;gdoc-hint note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__title flex align-center&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;global_ocean.cs32x15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__text&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;global ocean using the cubed-sphere grid 32x32x32 with 15 levels&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>coupled</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/coupled/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/coupled/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;MITgcm can be an atmosphere-ocean coupled model using its own coupler.&#xA;There is a verification called &lt;code&gt;cpl_aim+ocn&lt;/code&gt;, and it is a coupled version of atmospheric and oceanic model on cubed sphere grid that we did so far.&#xA;The instruction below can be found in &lt;code&gt;README&lt;/code&gt; file in &lt;code&gt;cpl_aim+ocn&lt;/code&gt; to run the coupled simulation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;gdoc-hint note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__title flex align-center&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_check&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;README.md&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;gdoc-hint__text&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h3 id=&#34;atmosphere-ocean-coupled-set-up-example-cpl_aimocn&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Atmosphere-Ocean coupled set-up example &amp;ldquo;cpl_aim+ocn&amp;rdquo;&#xA;    &lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;http://localhost:1313/research/MITgcm/coupled/#atmosphere-ocean-coupled-set-up-example-cpl_aimocn&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Atmosphere-Ocean coupled set-up example &amp;ldquo;cpl_aim&amp;#43;ocn&amp;rdquo;&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Atmosphere-Ocean coupled set-up example &amp;ldquo;cpl_aim&amp;#43;ocn&amp;rdquo;&#34; href=&#34;#atmosphere-ocean-coupled-set-up-example-cpl_aimocn&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;using simplified atmospheric physics (AIM), in realistic configuration (orography&#xA;&amp;amp; continent) with land and seaice component, on cubed-sphere (cs-32) grid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
